-- SHADOW-SEMANTICS cell D22 (#724): definer shadow of a method on a MULTI-TYPARAM
-- interface (`interface Ix a i`, two type params), in VALUE position.  d18 at
-- multi-typaram width -- the exact cell the corpus lacked (d18 is single-typaram
-- Sizeable; d11 is multi-typaram but an APP head).
--
-- The #410-class skew at multi-typaram width: the CHECK path grounds the value-position
-- definer shadow to the standalone scheme (`Int -> Int`) typaram-AGNOSTICally
-- (maybeStandaloneValueMono's definer arm gates on ifaceMethodName), but the EMIT path's
-- maybeStandaloneValueMonoEmit DECLINED it behind a blanket `singleTyparamIfaceMethod`
-- gate.  So `map size [1,2,3]` inferred element type `a -> i -> Int` (a function) on
-- build, and `println`'s `Display (List (Int -> Int))` stamped a NULL element dict
-- (RNone -> i64 0) -> the shipped binary SEGFAULTed (exit 139), while check and run were
-- clean [2, 3, 4].  Fixed 2026-07-19 by splitting maybeStandaloneValueMonoEmit's gate per
-- shadow kind (emitValueShadowGate): DEFINER arm is now ifaceMethodName (typaram-agnostic,
-- mirroring the check path), IMPORTER arm stays singleTyparamIfaceMethod (i10 / Fork 1).
-- Now ALL_EXACT [2, 3, 4] on check/run/build.
interface Ix a i where
  size : a -> i -> Int

data Box = Box Int

impl Ix Box Int where
  size (Box a) i = a + i

size : Int -> Int
size n = n + 1

main = println (map size [1, 2, 3])
